messages.content: Since those generated strikes don’t exhaust
odd
this is the core of how high noon works
I do not expect it not to work on not hermit-strikes/defends
hmm really

It's reasonable early as a way to get better frontloaded damage (not that champ really struggles there), and it has a lot of good synergies later in the game as well with strike of genius and murder strike being your best targets to double. Doubling strike of genius+ is particularly relevant as a way to add some extra oomph to champs sustained lategame damage, and is one of your few ways to take down neow through all the healing. Flurry of strikes is probably one of the better early game damage cards you can take as champ, since it transitions reasonably well to have some utility in the lategame, whereas most of their strong early game attacks fall off pretty hard in the lategame. Better with runic pyramid to help you line it up with the best possible targets to double. Upgrade is not a priority, just the standard +3. Decent with ninja relics, as it can help you trigger them 3 times by spending 2 energy on 2 cards.
